						               													<description>Sendas is a two player, abstract strategy board game.&amp;#10;The action takes place in a 9x9 grid board where players control 6 pieces each (differentiated by light and dark colors) starting from mirrored positions on opposite sides.&amp;#10;Players take turns moving and/or rotating one of their pieces in an attempt to reach the opposite side of the board and be the first to take one piece out of it. &amp;#10;The pieces are square blocks with a white line on top called &amp;ldquo;Senda&amp;rdquo; (&amp;ldquo;Path&amp;rdquo; in English) that comes in three shapes: a straight line, an elbow, a T or a + shape.&amp;#10;The only rule is that all pieces of the same color must stay connected to each other by the senda at all times. You can not make a move if it disconnects your pieces or your opponent's from the rest of the same color.&amp;#10;The sendas of both players can also be connected, creating one long senda that allows for pieces of both colors to get mixed in an intricate pattern.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
